<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="525" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1641,2026]" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1785,1810]" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Remarks.</emphasis>
To be conservative, we regard all specimens found by studies in 
<collectingRegion box="[996,1060,1785,1810]" country="Malaysia" name="Perak" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Perak</collectingRegion>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Herre &amp; Myers" authorityYear="1937" box="[1097,1222,1785,1810]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Tor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="525" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tambra">
<emphasis box="[1097,1222,1785,1810]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Tor tambra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the time being. Past literature has treated 
<emphasis box="[442,897,1821,1846]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Herre &amp; Myers" authorityYear="1937" box="[442,553,1821,1846]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Tor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="525" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tambra">T. tambra</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Herre &amp; Myers" authorityYear="1937" box="[565,721,1821,1846]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Tor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="525" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tambroides">T. tambroides</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[733,897,1821,1846]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Tor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="525" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="douronensis">T. douronensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="non Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[952,1027,1822,1845]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Tor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="525" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="soro">
<emphasis box="[952,1027,1822,1845]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">T. soro</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as valid species (
<bibRefCitation author="Nguyen, T. T. T. &amp; Na-Nakorn, U. &amp; Sukmanomon, S. &amp; ZiMing, C." box="[1226,1383,1822,1846]" pageId="10" pageNumber="525" pagination="1223 - 1231" refId="ref17677" refString="Nguyen, T. T. T., Na-Nakorn, U., Sukmanomon, S. &amp; ZiMing, C. (2008) A study on phylogeny and biogeography of mahseer species (Pisces: Cyprinidae) using sequences of three mitochondrial DNA gene regions. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 48, 1223 - 1231. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2008.01.006" type="journal article" year="2008">Nguyen 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Esa, Y. B. &amp; Rahim, K. A. A." pageId="10" pageNumber="525" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref14982" refString="Esa, Y. B. &amp; Rahim, K. A. A. (2013) Genetic structure and preliminary findings of cryptic diversity of the Malaysian Mahseer (Tor tambroides Valenciennes: Cyprinidae) inferred from mitochondrial DNA and microsatellite analyses. BioMed Research International, 1 - 14. https: // doi. org / 10.1155 / 2013 / 170980" type="book chapter" year="2013">
Esa 
<emphasis box="[151,217,1857,1882]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">et al.,</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Norfatimah, M. Y. &amp; Teh, L. K. &amp; Salleh, M. Z. &amp; Mat Isa, M. N. &amp; SitiAzizah, M. N." box="[300,575,1857,1882]" pageId="10" pageNumber="525" pagination="263 - 269" refId="ref17775" refString="Norfatimah, M. Y., Teh, L. K., Salleh, M. Z., Mat Isa, M. N. &amp; SitiAzizah, M. N. (2014) Complete mitochondrial genome of Malaysian Mahseer (Tor tambroides). Gene, 548, 263 - 269. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. gene. 2014.07.044" type="journal article" year="2014">
Norfatimah 
<emphasis box="[438,504,1857,1882]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">et al.,</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="non Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[596,673,1858,1881]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Tor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="525" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="soro">
<emphasis box="[596,673,1858,1881]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">T. soro</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is now valid as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fricke et al., 2018)" authorityName="Fricke" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Fricke" baseAuthorityYear="2018" box="[869,1336,1857,1882]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Neolissochilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="525" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="soro">
<emphasis box="[869,1092,1857,1882]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Neolissochilus soro</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fricke, R. &amp; Eschmeyer, W. N. &amp; van der Laan, R." box="[1108,1328,1857,1882]" pageId="10" pageNumber="525" refId="ref15047" refString="Fricke, R., Eschmeyer, W. N. &amp; van der Laan, R. (eds) (2018) Catalogue of Fishes: Genera, Species, References. California Academy of Sciences. Available from http: // researcharchive. calacademy. org / research / ichthyology / catalog / fishcatmain. asp (Accessed 20 October 2018)" type="url" year="2018">
Fricke 
<emphasis box="[1191,1250,1857,1882]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">et al.</emphasis>
, 2018
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Roberts, T. R." pageId="10" pageNumber="525" pagination="225 - 236" refId="ref18096" refString="Roberts, T. R. (1999) Fishes of the cyprinid genus Tor in the Nam Theun watershed (Mekong Basin) of Laos, with description of a new species. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 47 (1), 225 - 236." type="journal article" year="1999">Roberts (1999)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Kottelat, M." box="[282,454,1893,1918]" pageId="10" pageNumber="525" pagination="1 - 663" refId="ref15672" refString="Kottelat, M. (2013) The fishes of the inland waters of Southeast Asia: A catalogue and core bibliography of the fishes known to occur in freshwaters, mangroves and estuaries. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 27, 1 - 663." type="journal article" year="2013">Kottelat (2013)</bibRefCitation>
were unable to conclusively determine the unique morphological markers between the mentioned species. They have also treated 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[655,823,1929,1954]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Tor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="525" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="douronensis">
<emphasis box="[655,823,1929,1954]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">T. douronensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Herre &amp; Myers" authorityYear="1937" box="[1094,1205,1929,1954]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Tor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="525" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tambra">
<emphasis box="[1094,1205,1929,1954]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">T. tambra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A recent study by 
<bibRefCitation author="Walton, S. E. &amp; Gan, H. M. &amp; Raghavan, R. &amp; Pinder, A. &amp; Ahmad, A." box="[151,377,1965,1990]" pageId="10" pageNumber="525" pagination="171 - 183" refId="ref18901" refString="Walton, S. E., Gan, H. M., Raghavan, R., Pinder, A. &amp; Ahmad, A. (2017) Disentangling the Taxonomy of the Mahseers (Tor spp.) of Malaysia: An Integrated Approach Using Morphology, Genetics and Historical Records. Reviews in Fisheries Science and Aquaculture, 171 - 183." type="book chapter" year="2017">
Walton 
<emphasis box="[238,295,1965,1990]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">et al.</emphasis>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
also does not support multiple species designation for 
<taxonomicName box="[996,1031,1966,1989]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Tor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="525" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[996,1031,1966,1989]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Tor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that occurs in Peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[1326,1432,1965,1990]" name="Malaysia" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
. Thus, following 
<bibRefCitation author="Kottelat, M." box="[337,511,2001,2026]" pageId="10" pageNumber="525" pagination="1 - 663" refId="ref15672" refString="Kottelat, M. (2013) The fishes of the inland waters of Southeast Asia: A catalogue and core bibliography of the fishes known to occur in freshwaters, mangroves and estuaries. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 27, 1 - 663." type="journal article" year="2013">Kottelat (2013)</bibRefCitation>
, our checklist adopted the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Herre &amp; Myers" authorityYear="1937" box="[878,986,2001,2026]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Tor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="525" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tambra">
<emphasis box="[878,986,2001,2026]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">T. tambra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for specimens found in 
<collectingRegion box="[1258,1325,2001,2026]" country="Malaysia" name="Perak" pageId="10" pageNumber="525">Perak</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
